@Node "Requirements" "ADGLookUp | Requirements"

  This  program  requires,  that  you  "translate" your ordinary AutoDocs to the
guide format, by using the AD2AG (or AD2HT).  This program creates a file called
'autodocs.xref'.   ADGLookUp.ced  uses  this  file  as  a  cross  reference (See
@{"Installation and SetUp"  Link  "Installation"  }  to  see,  how to tell ADGLookUp.ced where to  look  for
the  xref  file.).   I don't know, if you need OS2.04, or if this works with pre
2.04,  since  I  don't  feel  like  spending  any time on pre 2.04 - get 2.04 or
higher!  
@EndNode 
@Node "Installation" "ADGLookUp | Installation & SetUp"

  I'm  no  wizard in programming the installation script, so the installation is
left for you to do manually.  But this is also easy!  Just copy the ADLookUp.ced
script  to  the rexx:  or the rexx:ced/ drawer.  Then start CygnusEd and install
the command on a Function key, by using the "Special->DOS/ARexx Interface" menu,
and select "Install DOS/Arexx command..." or create a macro on the help key.

  Then  you  must edit the script to make sure, that it's setup for your system.
The  lines  that  must  be  changed,  is line 45 through 45.  Explanation of the
options  is  found  in  the  rexx-script.   If setup is not correct, you will be
notified!
@EndNode
@Node "Usage" "ADGLookUp | Usage"

  When  configured  correct, simply press your hotkey on the keyword you want to
search  for.   And a few seconds later, the amigaguide will pop up, if any match
of keyword is found, otherwise you will be notified.  You will also be notified,
if setup is not correct.

Note:   It will search for any word you're on, also if it's not a valid keyword.
If  such  search  is started, then a search will fail.  You can stop a search by
starting the program 'hi' from any shell.
@EndNode
@Node "Options" "ADGLookUp | Options"

  The program can not be called with any options. You should set options within
the file. See @{"Installation and SetUp"  Link  "Installation"  }!
@EndNode
